text.section:
Notwithstanding any other law, a claim on money in the escrow account has the following priorities in this order:
payments ordered by the Attorney General or a court under § 11-625 of Part II of this subtitle;
subrogation claims of the State under § 11-817 of this title;
a court order of restitution under § 11-603 of this subtitle;
a civil judgment of a victim or victim's representative; and
a civil judgment of a person, other than a victim or victim's representative, arising out of the crime.
